com.hcl.domino.richtext.structures

Interface MemoryStructureWrapperService


  • public interface MemoryStructureWrapperService
    This interface represents a service capable of wrapping ByteBuffers into MemoryStructure instances in an implementation-specific way.
    Since:
    1.0.15
    Author:
    Jesse Gallagher

      • wrapStructure

        <T extends MemoryStructure> T wrapStructure(Class<T> structureClass,
                                            ByteBuffer data)
        Wraps the provided ByteBuffer into an instance of the provided structure class, without appending it to the destination rich-text entity. This is useful in specific situations where variable data consists of structured values.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of structure contained in the data
        Parameters:
        structureClass - a Class representing <T>
        data - the data to wrap
        Returns:
        the newly-wrapped structure
